title: Yolov4
description: State of the art facial detection with the Yolov4 architecture.
architectureDescription: A darknet50 backend with novel Yolo heads.

antiGoals.description: Resolving distinct identities for people in crowds (i.e. facial recognition)
Any goal designed for very specialized, mission critical identification scenarios.

ethicalConsiderations.description: People should not be using this for bad things. In the future, more testing is needed with a more diverse dataset.
People should use this for good things!

performanceOverview: We trained this model card with Yolov4 Traning procedures directly from the darknet repo. It required a lot of work and a lot of things, and did very well.

limitations.description: This model becomes a lot less accurate once figures are occluded.
This model will detect at medium accuracy, faces that are printed on pieces of paper and presented to to the model.
Because this network was trained on the CelebA dataset, made up of majority caucasian people, the network may not detect people of other skintones with as high of accuracy.

intendedUse.primaryGoal: To help people on social media better tag themselves and other friends in pictures.

datasets.name: COCO (custom)
datasets.description: A custom subset of the coco dataset.

primaryGoal: To help social media users better use social media.

stakeholderImpacts.impact: Innocent bystanders may be accidentally classified with this model without their consent.
